JAPAN DAYBOOK: Japanese Stocks May Rise as Nuclear Fears Ease

-- B y   S t e v e   M c P h e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-22T00:01:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/japan-daybook-japanese-stocks-may-rise-as-nuclear-fears-ease.html
Japanese  stock futures  rose as the
country made progress in stabilizing reactors at a crippled
nuclear plant. American depositary receipts of Toyota, Honda
and Nissan jumped more than 5% before Japan’s equity markets
open for business after the long weekend today.  WHAT TO WATCH
*Economic and Fiscal Policy Minister  Kaoru Yosano  says Japan
could pay for earthquake reconstruction through spending cuts,
bond sales or a change to the tax system
*Crews may resume spraying water on damaged nuclear reactors.
Tepco yesterday stopped the operation after smoke was seen
coming out of the No.3 reactor
*Containment units at Fukushima nuclear reactors intact, U.S.
commission says; situation near “stabilizing”
*Japan likely to see a rebound in 2H, economist survey says;
banks split on whether  Japan  will experience recession
*Japan quake may cost life insurers $4.9b, Moody’s says;
domestic insurers most impacted
*Morning cabinet meeting followed by minister briefings
*Treasury discount bill auction results 12:35 p.m.
*Condominium supply February 1 p.m.
*All industry activity index January 1:30 pm. Forecast +2.8%.
*Supermarket sales February 2 p.m.
*Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Edano briefing 4 p.m. 